Cell["\<\
The differences are not in the queries but in device noise: each shot passes \
through a deep transpiled circuit on superconducting hardware, and the noise \
varies from job to job.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"029084e5-3afd-4136-9999-ddc3a73f8403"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Amazon Braket", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"38374488-9e1e-42b0-969a-93f6e42e0560"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Amazon Braket is a quantum computing service on ",
 ButtonBox["Amazon Web Services",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://aws.amazon.com/"], None}],
 " (AWS). Unlike IBM, which exposes its own superconducting devices, Braket \
fronts several vendors (IonQ, Rigetti, QuEra and others) and on-demand \
simulators through one API, which makes it convenient for comparing \
technologies side by side. The Wolfram Language reaches it through the \
standard AWS service connection."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f190e9b1-618c-4520-99c7-e196f60fa393"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Connecting to AWS", "Subsection",ExpressionUUID->"9e2ccfce-9425-4175-9281-e6678954225f"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "Connect to AWS with your credentials (access key ID and secret access key); \
see the workflow ",
 ButtonBox["Authenticate with Amazon Web Services",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://reference.wolfram.com/language/workflow/\
AuthenticateWithAmazonWebServices.html"], None}],
 " for details on storing them:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6323c042-a4a4-43b2-a83e-d4c733ffafe1"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"aws", " ", "=", " ", 
  RowBox[{"ServiceConnect", "[", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<AWS\>\"", ",", " ", "\"\<New\>\""}], "]"}]}]], "Input",Express\
ionUUID->"3d3c99b8-62bd-47b7-abff-0b328541aa64"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "Braket writes every task result to an S3 bucket, so you reach two AWS \
services through the connection: S3 for storage and Braket for the quantum \
tasks. If you do not have an S3 bucket yet, ",
 ButtonBox["create one",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://s3.console.aws.amazon.com/"], None}],
 " first:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"69a28484-3154-4793-9f2c-e912a89d9bb3"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"s3", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"ServiceExecute", "[", 
    RowBox[{"aws", ",", " ", "\"\<GetService\>\"", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<Name\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "\"\<S3\>\""}], "}"}]}], 
    "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"braket", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"ServiceExecute", "[", 
    RowBox[{"aws", ",", " ", "\"\<GetService\>\"", ",", " ", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<Name\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "\"\<Braket\>\""}], "}"}]}], 
    "]"}]}], ";"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[16]:=",ExpressionUUID->"e358862c-26f6-49e0-b79d-4aa5d5436a22"],

